Movie: Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Dog Days
Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Rodrick Rules

Review: Still a good amount of heart but too much going on

An excellent film which makes all of its characters really feel alive. It uses humor very well to tackle otherwise unapproachable subject matter. Great soundtrack too. The ending dragged on a bit for me.

One of the best films ever made. A satire that doesn't lose the idea of just how scary it's target is by giving them compelling character development beyond simple incompetence. A love letter to cinema and a movie that feels nowhere near as long as it's run time. Best of all it is not that star studded. It allows space for lesser known actors to embody their role and they do it well. A movie that makes sure death actually means something and one which keeps you on your toes. Will be rewatching again soon.
